# UI/UX Enhancement Walkthrough

This document summarizes the interactive and visual improvements made to the SiDispen mobile application.

## 1. Entrance & Transition Animations
We implemented a staggered entrance system to make the app feel "alive" as it loads.
- **`AnimatedEntrance.tsx`**: A reusable component that handles fade, scale, and slide transitions.
- **Dashboards**: Applied to all role-based dashboards (Siswa, Piket, Wali, Ortu) for headers, cards, and list items.
- **Login Screen**: Staggered reveal of the login form elements.

## 2. Typewriter Effect
The welcome message on the login screen now features a typewriter animation.
- **File**: [login.tsx](file:///c:/laragon/www/SIdispen%20(SMA%203)/mobile-app/app/login.tsx)
- **Effect**: "Selamat Datang!" types out character by character upon entry.

## 3. Animated Statistics
Counters and charts now animate their values instead of showing them statically.
- **`AnimatedCounter.tsx`**: Used for numeric statistics (e.g., total tickets, counts).
- **`DonutChart.tsx`**: Added a "drawing" SVG animation for the attendance ring in the Wali dashboard.

## 4. Gesture-Based Interactions
Improved the "feel" of interactions using native gesture handlers.
- **Bottom Sheet Migration**: [RejectModal.tsx](file:///c:/laragon/www/SIdispen%20(SMA%203)/mobile-app/src/components/RejectModal.tsx) now uses `@gorhom/bottom-sheet`, providing a liquid, swipeable interaction for rejecting tickets.
- **Gesture Root**: Configured `GestureHandlerRootView` globally in [\_layout.tsx](file:///c:/laragon/www/SIdispen%20(SMA%203)/mobile-app/app/_layout.tsx).

## 5. Micro-Animations
Subtle visual cues to guide the user's attention.
- **Pulse Effects**: Added to the [TopAppBar](file:///c:/laragon/www/SIdispen%20(SMA%203)/mobile-app/src/components/TopAppBar.tsx) notification dot and [PillBadge](file:///c:/laragon/www/SIdispen%20(SMA%203)/mobile-app/src/components/PillBadge.tsx) for active statuses.
- **Haptic Feedback**: Integrated light haptics into toggles and buttons.

## 6. Shimmer Loading States (Optional)
Prepared `ShimmerPlaceholder.tsx` for future use in data-heavy screens to maintain the glass-morphism aesthetic during network requests.

